                <truckmodel>9400</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9600</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9700</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9800</truckmodel>
                <ucodegroup/>

                <ucode>14UJG</ucode>
                <ucode>14UJH</ucode>
                <vendcodegroup/>

                <vendcode>HA-460-55</vendcode>
                <vendcode>HA-460-60</vendcode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The air ride suspension is a smooth, shock and vibration free ride with a preset constant
                        frame height.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The air springs (bags) on the air suspension take the place of steel springs, therefore there
                        is no interleaf friction to overcome. Thereby, minimum road shock is transferred to the frame,
                        cargo and driver (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300701">Figure 1</hotlnk>and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0300702">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <figure id="f0300701" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0300701" filename="../figg03/G0300701.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 1. SINGLE AXLE SUSPENSION</caption>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <figure id="f0300702" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0300702" filename="../figg03/G0300702.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2. TANDEM AXLE SUSPENSION</caption>
                    </figure>
                </lev1>
                <lev1>
                    <para>The air ride suspension adjusts to load changes automatically, providing a low rate suspension
                        with a light or no load condition, and a higher rate suspension with heavier loads. The major
                        components of the air ride suspension system, whether used on single or tandem axles, are
                        described in the following text.
                    </para>
                </lev1>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
